gar’s fullservice capability includes waste stream prequalification unloading and processing of rcra hazardous and nonhazardous solids and liquids gar can accept a wide variation of waste materials to include but not limited to refinery still bottoms paint solids tars solvents degreasers offspec chemicals dry powders debris and etc acceptable waste containers include drums end dumps totes rolloffs sludgevacuum boxes tank trucks cubic yard boxes and bags rail intermodels rail tankers rail gondolas processing systems center around totally enclosed blending and processing buildings that vent organic vapors to the burning zone of the kiln processing facilities operate  hours a day seven days a week deliveries are typically accepted monday through friday and delivery times are established in accordance with a prearranged scheduling including the flexibility of “drop and swap” gar operates a fully capable waste fuel laboratory offering onsite analytical services to meet facility processing and regulatory analytical requirements locations green america recycling llc  highway hannibal mo  view details home  continental cement established leader in environmental stewardship learn more welcome to continental cement company llc a whollyowned subsidiary of summit materials nyse sum we have two manufacturing facilities located in davenport iowa and hannibal missouri with distribution facilities in des moines iowa and along the mississippi river from minneapolis minnesota to new orleans louisiana our corporate office is located in chesterfield missouri about us latest newsmore july  by it help desk cement plant earns epa’s energy star certification continental cement has earned the us environmental protection agency’s epa’s energy star certification which signifies that the facility performs in the top  percent of similar facilities nationwide for energy efficiency and meets strict energy efficiency performance levels set by the epa continental cement improved its energy performa